'''阮丹桂'''（{{lang-vi|Nguyễn Đan Quế}}，{{bd|1942年|4月13日<ref name=AI>{{cite web |url=http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/ASA41/019/2004/en/4de3291f-d59c-11dd-bb24-1fb85fe8fa05/asa410192004en.pdf |title=Viet Nam: High cost of lifelong commitment to human rights |date=18 August 2004 |publisher=Amnesty International |accessdate=21 July 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110310233652/http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/ASA41/019/2004/en/4de3291f-d59c-11dd-bb24-1fb85fe8fa05/asa410192004en.pdf |archivedate=2011年3月10日 }}</ref>||}}）是[[越南|越南]]的一位[[内分泌|内分泌]]学家，他更为著名的身份是[[持不同政見者|持不同政見者]]、[[人權|人權]]活動家、民运人士和[[良心犯|良心犯]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/11/24/world/vietnam-hopeful-on-ties-after-talks-in-the-us.html |title=Vietnam Hopeful on Ties After Talks in the U.S |author=Barbara Crossette |date=24 November 1991 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525232152/http://www.nytimes.com/1991/11/24/world/vietnam-hopeful-on-ties-after-talks-in-the-us.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=NYT235 />他曾在1978年至1988年、2003年至2005年、2011年至今三次因为宣传[[越南民主运动|民主运动]]，而被越南共产当局以危害国家安全的罪名逮捕入狱。《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》在2003年对他的一篇报道中称赞他是“越南最有声誉的[[异见人士|异见人士]]”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/04/05/opinion/the-world-s-other-tyrants-still-at-work.html?pagewanted=2 |title=The World's Other Tyrants, Still at Work |author=Aryeh Neier |date=5 April 2003 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151118120457/http://www.nytimes.com/2003/04/05/opinion/the-world-s-other-tyrants-still-at-work.html?pagewanted=2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==生平==
阮丹桂於1942年出生在[[河內市|河內]]，当时河内处在日本皇军的占领之下。[[日内瓦会议_(1954年)|日内瓦会议]]结束之后，越南北部被共产主义势力控制，父母带着他的五个兄弟姐妹一起逃到南部的[[胡志明市|西贡]]（今[[胡志明市|胡志明市]]）。<ref name="rallyingfordemocracy.org">[http://www.rallyingfordemocracy.org/index.php?page=blog&title=Who+is+Dr.+Nguyen+Dan+Que%3F]</ref>他在22岁的时候取得[[西贡大学|西贡大学]][[医学士|医学士]]的学位。在20世纪60至70年代间，他获得[[联合国|联合国]]的奖金，去[[欧洲|欧洲]]专攻[[放射性疗法|放射性疗法]]。<ref name=AI/>

1974年，他到西贡大学执教。翌年，成为Chợ Rẫy医院的负责人。[[西贡沦陷|西贡沦陷]]后，他本有机会逃离越南，但却决定留下向穷人提供医疗帮助。<ref name="rallyingfordemocracy.org"/>

然而在第二年，阮丹桂就因为批评共产当局对健康照顾的区别政策而被免职。<ref name=AI/><ref name="rallyingfordemocracy.org"/>他随后组建了亲民主的组织——民族進步阵线（Mặt trận Dân tộc Tiến bộ）。<ref name=NYT811/>他也是[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]在越南的第一位成员，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1992/01/05/magazine/reaching-for-the-good-life-in-vietnam.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=Reaching for the Good Life in Vietnam |author=Philip Shenon |date=5 January 1992 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306203907/http://www.nytimes.com/1992/01/05/magazine/reaching-for-the-good-life-in-vietnam.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref>开始出版了两个地下报刊向公众发行，对当局违反人权的行径提出质问，建议当局减少军事开支，投资于百姓福利之上。<ref name=AI/><ref name="rallyingfordemocracy.org"/>1978年，他因为继续批判过当局的健康保护政策，<ref name=BBC291/>与47名同志一起被捕，未经任何审判便关入监狱。他们在狱中备受酷刑折磨，其中五人在监禁中死去。当阮丹桂提出要提高政治犯的待遇时，他被禁闭在一个五到六英尺的、没有任何卫生设施的笼子里长达两个月。他后来被判处十年监禁。<ref name=NYT811/>

他被释放后，又组建了一个民主运动组织——人本高潮（Cao Trào Nhân Bản）。1990年6月14日，他又被当局逮捕。<ref name=AI/><ref name=NYT811/>1991年11月29日，因为向国际特赦组织送出信件，被当局以[[叛国罪|叛国罪]]判处20年[[劳动改造|劳动改造]]外加5年的软禁于家中。[[越共|越共]]的喉舌称“[[反动|反动]]势力利用他们来诽谤越南”以及“试图推翻人民政府”。<ref name="rallyingfordemocracy.org"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/12/04/world/vietnamese-rights-advocate-is-said-to-get-20-year-term.html |title=Vietnamese Rights Advocate Is Said to Get 20-Year Term |date=4 December 1991 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525223819/http://www.nytimes.com/1991/12/04/world/vietnamese-rights-advocate-is-said-to-get-20-year-term.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>阮丹桂的家人和人权组织报导称当局不顾他日渐恶劣的健康状况，把他分配去做艰苦的劳动。越南外交部否认了这些指控。<ref name=NYT811>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1993/11/08/world/hanoi-is-accused-of-abusing-critic.html |title=Hanoi is Accused of Abusing Critic |author=Philip Shenon |date=8 November 1993 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526090123/http://www.nytimes.com/1993/11/08/world/hanoi-is-accused-of-abusing-critic.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1991年4月，美国参议员{{link-en|鲍勃·克里|Bob Kerrey}}试图再次与他的家人会面，遭到当局的拒绝。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/04/29/opinion/our-saigon-friends-still-need-help.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=Our Saigon Friends Still Need Help |author=James Webb |date=29 April 1991 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306072617/http://www.nytimes.com/1991/04/29/opinion/our-saigon-friends-still-need-help.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref>1993年8月，参议员{{link-en|查克·罗伯|Chuck Robb}}位于阮丹桂弟弟居住的选区内，试图与阮丹桂接触并向他送去药品，被越南当局禁止跟他会面。<ref name=NYT235>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1994/05/23/world/vietnam-revisited-periodic-report-security-tactics-vietnam-still-inspire.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=Vietnam Revisited: A periodic report.; Security Tactics in Vietnam Still Inspire Widespread Fear |author=Malcolm W. Browne |date=23 May 1994 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305133027/http://www.nytimes.com/1994/05/23/world/vietnam-revisited-periodic-report-security-tactics-vietnam-still-inspire.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1993/08/20/world/hanoi-bars-a-senator-s-visit-with-dissident.html |title=Hanoi Bars a Senator's Visit With Dissident |date=20 August 1993 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821213012/http://www.nytimes.com/1993/08/20/world/hanoi-bars-a-senator-s-visit-with-dissident.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>阮丹桂案被[[欧洲议会|欧洲议会]]、<ref name=NYT298/>[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]和[[法国|法国]]所接受。<ref name=BBC298 />

1998年越南发布大赦令，阮丹桂和另一位民主运动家[[段曰活|段曰活]]一起获释。二人被准许离开越南去[[美国|美国]]，美国还提供了居住地。<ref name=NYT298>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1998/08/29/world/world-news-briefs-an-amnesty-in-vietnam-includes-some-americans.html |title=World News Briefs; An Amnesty in Vietnam Includes Some Americans |date=29 August 1998 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306074532/http://www.nytimes.com/1998/08/29/world/world-news-briefs-an-amnesty-in-vietnam-includes-some-americans.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>但阮丹桂拒绝了，他声明就算呆在监狱里都比被迫流亡好。<ref name=BBC298>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/160676.stm |title=Vietnamese dissident refuses to leave |date=29 August 1998 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151118093758/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/160676.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>此后他继续留在了越南。

1999年5月12日，阮丹桂在互联网上发表声明，要求[[越南国会|越南国会]]实现自由选举，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1999/05/12/world/world-briefing.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |title=Vietnam: Dissident Speaks Out |author=Seth Mydans |date=12 May 1993 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306221734/http://www.nytimes.com/1999/05/12/world/world-briefing.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |dead-url=no }}</ref>此后数日，他又发布了数篇批评越南媒体审查的文章。他因此在17日再次被捕，当局指控他从事间谍活动。<ref name="rallyingfordemocracy.org"/><ref name="BBC News">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-pacific-12595261 |title=Vietnam activist Nguyen Dan Que held for uprising call |date=28 February 2011 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2013-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119083752/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-pacific-12595261 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2004年1月29日，胡志明市人民法院认定他“散布民主权力言论，危害国家互联网以及合法权利、社会组织和人民的利益”，判处30个月的监禁。<ref name=BBC291>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/3935519.stm |title=Vietnam jails veteran dissident |date=29 January 2004 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306013321/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/3935519.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>他在2005年1月因为春节而获得特赦，与阮文理、Nguyen Dinh Huy、Huynh Van Ba一起出狱。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4222479.stm |title=Vietnam to free top dissidents |date=31 January 2005 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151201012714/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4222479.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2011年2月中旬，阮丹桂在互联网上发布信息，试图以[[阿拉伯之春|阿拉伯之春]]的模式推动越南拥有更多的民主，被当局指控企圖推翻政府而遭到逮捕，<ref name=WP>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/28/AR2011022800803.html |title=Vietnam dissident detained for revolution calls |author=Margie Mason |date=28 February 2011 |work=The Washington Post |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2017-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316012325/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/28/AR2011022800803.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>其後曾獲准保釋<ref>[http://www.voanews.com/chinese/news/20110301-VIETNAM-DISSIDENT-117128903.html 越南異議人士阮丹桂交保釋放 (美國之音新聞)]</ref>。警方对他家进行突袭之后，宣称在他家发现上千份反政府文件。国际特赦组织认为他是良心犯，呼吁越南当局释放他。2012年3月6日，美国前众议院议员[[高光映|高光映]]开展了一项游说越南当局释放阮丹桂、[[阮文理_(人權活動家)|阮文理]]、[[阮文海_(持不同政见者)|阮文海]]等政治犯的活动，要求[[奥巴马|奥巴马]]总统和[[美国国会|美国国会]]向越南当局施压。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nola.com/politics/index.ssf/2012/03/former_rep_cao_back_on_capitol.html |title=Former Rep. Anh 'Joseph' Cao urges tougher line against Vietnam |author=Jonathan Tilove |date=7 March 2012 |work=The Times-Picayune |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151203110134/http://www.nola.com/politics/index.ssf/2012/03/former_rep_cao_back_on_capitol.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==奖项==
阮丹桂在1995年获得[[罗伯特·弗朗西斯·肯尼迪人权奖|罗伯特·弗朗西斯·肯尼迪人权奖]]，以表彰他对越南的自由和人权作出的贡献。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rfkcenter.org/1995-dr-nguyen-dan-que-viet-nam |title=1995: Dr. Nguyen Dan Que, Viet Nam |year=1995 |publisher=Robert F. Kennedy Human Rights Award |accessdate=21 July 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130620185931/http://rfkcenter.org/1995-dr-nguyen-dan-que-viet-nam |archivedate=2013-06-20}}</ref>2004年，他获得[[公民勇气奖|公民勇气奖]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.civilcourageprize.org/index.htm |title=Civil Courage Prize |year=2012 |publisher=Civil Courage Prize |accessdate=10 August 2012 |archive-date=2012-08-11 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/69qPLl2L5?url=http://www.civilcourageprize.org/index.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

